2. Functions in SQL:  

â™¦ DateTime Functions
  strftime("%Y", column)  -- Year
  strftime("%m", column)  -- Month
  strftime("%d", column)  -- Day
  strftime("%H", column)  -- Hour
  strftime("%M", column)  -- Minute  
  strftime("%j", column)  -- Day of the year 

â™¦ Typecasting Function
  CAST(strftime("%Y", column) AS INTEGER) = 2025  
  ðŸ”´Note: By default, datetime is stored as a string.  

â™¦ Arithmetic Functions 
  FLOOR(column_name)  -- Down round-off to left number before decimal point  
  CEIL(column_name)   -- Upper round-off   
  ROUND(column_name, decimals)  -- Round to specified decimal places   

â™¦ String Functions
  UPPER(column_name)  -- Convert to UPPERCASE  
  LOWER(column_name)  -- Convert to lowercase  
