3. CASE Statement :
â™¦ Used in: SELECT, WHERE, GROUP BY, HAVING  

  CASE  
    WHEN condition1 THEN result1  
    WHEN condition2 THEN result2  
    ELSE default_result  
  END  
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. Set Operations : 
â™¦ INTERSECT             - same items in both results
â™¦ MINUS / EXCEPT        - unique items in Left item set
â™¦ UNION                 - all items in both queries unique 1 time
â™¦ UNION ALL             - all items even duplicates/repetitions results

ðŸ”´Note: To perform set operations, in select of both queries must have
1. Same number of columns
2. Same data types columns
3. Same column order
